Description.
Female (
Holotype
, 
Guyana
, BMNH). Total length 9.44. Carapace 3.81 long, 3.32 wide, yellow; unmarked. Clypeus yellow, 0.51 high. Anterior eye row straight, 0.98 wide; posterior recurved, 1.22 wide. Eye diameters, interdistances, and median ocular quadrangle: AME 0.14, ALE 0.12, PME 0.22, PLE 0.16; AME-AME 0.14, AME-ALE 0.21, PME-PME 0.24, PME-PLE 0.20, OQA 0.46, OQP 0.64, OQH 0.44. Chelicerae yellow. Sternum yellow, with scattered bristles; 1.82 long, 1.90 wide. Labium yellow, 0.40 long, 0.55 wide. Legs yellow, unmarked, with numerous dark brown macrosetae; relative length: I-II-IV-III, I—femur 6.72/ patella-tibia 9.57/ metatarsus 6.78/ tarsus 2.52/ total 25.59; II—7.05/ 9.31/ 6.65/ 2.50/ 25.51; III—5.81/ 7.04/ 5.05/ 1.99/ 19.89; IV—6.73/ 8.11/ 6.74/ 2.65/ 24.23. Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae: I-5; II-5; III-4; IV-4. Superior tarsal claw with ten teeth, median with one tooth (
Fig. 83
). Abdomen 4.64 long, light brown with an irregular dark brown patch on cardiac area; with scattered bristles and two pair of sigillae. Venter yellow, with scattered bristles. Epigynum with a well developed “hood-like” middle field (
Fig. 78
) and an acute posterior margin (
Fig. 80
). Head of spermathecae with slightly projected pores (
Fig. 82
) and short copulatory ducts (
Fig. 81
).

Male (Una, 
Bahia
, 
Brazil
, IBSP 47144). Total length 8.13. Carapace 3.81 long, 3.32 wide, as in female. Clypeus yellow, 0.40 high. Anterior eye row straight, 0.98 wide (
Fig. 14
); posterior recurved, 1.20 wide. Eye diameters, interdistances, and median ocular quadrangle: AME 0.22, ALE 0.12, PME 0.20, PLE 0.18; AME-AME 0.10, AME-ALE 0.14, PME-PME 0.20, PME-PLE 0.22, OQA 0.52, OQP 0.62, OQH 0.51. Chelicerae yellow, with scattered white bristles (
Fig. 14
). Sternum yellow, 1.82 long, 1.90 wide. Labium as in female, 0.33 long, 0.66 wide. Legs yellow, unmarked; relative length: I-II-IV-III, I—femur 8.77/ patella-tibia 12.23/ metatarsus 9.70/ tarsus 3.19/ total 33.89; II—8.64/ 11.30/ 8.40/ 2.92/ 31.26; III—6.65/ 7.98/ 5.98/ 2.26/ 22.87; IV—7.98/ 9.97/ 8.77/ 3.30/ 30.02. Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae: I-5; II-5; III-4; IV-4. Abdomen 4.06 long, colouration as in female. Palpus with a rounded apex of the median apophysis (
Fig. 84
); distal tegular projection short (
Fig. 84
). Ental branch of RTA with a slender and ventrally curved tip (
Figs 85, 86
); ectal branch of RTA with a subtriangular shape and a broad base (
Fig. 87
).
